race.comment: PIERATA'S GEM (15) was ridden quieter last start over 1350m at this track and wound up nicely to grab second in a BM70 for the mares. Gets beyond 1400m for the first time but drops 5.5kgs and the last effort suggested she needs this trip now. BENGAL DIAMOND (7) made it two wins from her last three starts when thrashed a similar field here at this trip a fortnight ago. In form mare who goes up 3kgs but if she repeats the last effort that might not matter. MAKE A CALL (3) came from nowhere to get up and win first-up over 1350m at this track two weeks ago. Doesn't usually perform second-up but his 1600m form here is impressive. ROCK HARD LOVE (5) couldn't go with BENGAL DIAMOND last start but is an each-way hope.
